The HAS_LABEL conditional rule is used to allow entities with the specified label. It is a condition in Red Hat Developer Hub that can be used to filter resources based on their labels. The rule is part of the catalog plugin schema and is used to match entities with a specific label. The rule is defined as follows:

```json
{
  "name": "HAS_LABEL",
  "description": "Allow entities with the specified label",
  "resourceType": "catalog-entity",
  "paramsSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "label": {
        "type": "string",
        "description": "Name of the label to match on"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

This rule can be used to filter resources based on their labels, for example, to display only resources with a specific label. The rule is part of the RBAC backend plugin and is used to construct a condition JSON object based on the previous condition schema.

