Based on the provided knowledge search results, the answer to the user's query "How to use placeholder for layout" is:

You can use the Placeholder card to arrange and adjust the dimensions of your cards using the drag-and-drop and resize functionality. To show the cards in three columns, define the x parameter as shown in the following example:

```yaml
dynamicPlugins:
  frontend:
    red-hat-developer-hub.backstage-plugin-dynamic-home-page:
      mountPoints:
        - mountPoint: home.page/cards
          importName: Placeholder
          config:
            layouts:
              xl: { w: 4, h: 2 }
              lg: { w: 4, h: 2 }
              md: { w: 4, h: 2 }
              sm: { w: 6, h: 2 }
              xs: { w: 12, h: 2 }
              xxs: { w: 12, h: 2 }
            props:
              showBorder: true
              debugContent: left
        - mountPoint: home.page/cards
          importName: Placeholder
          config:
            layouts:
              xl: { w: 4, h: 2, x: 4 }
              lg: { w: 4, h: 2, x: 4 }
              md: { w: 4, h: 2, x: 4 }
              sm: { w: 6, h: 2, x: 6 }
              xs: { w: 12, h: 2 }
              xxs: { w: 12, h: 2, x: 0 }
```

This will show the cards in three columns. You can also use the TemplateSection card to quickly explore and initiate software templates in RHDH.

