The IS_OWNER rule in RHDH is a conditional policy that allows entities owned by a specified claim. It can be used to display catalogs only if the user is a member of the owner group. The rule is defined as follows:

```json
{
  "rule": "IS_ENTITY_OWNER",
  "resourceType": "catalog-entity",
  "params": {
    "claims": ["group:default/team-a"]
  }
}
```

This rule can be applied to the RBAC REST API by adding additional parameters as follows:

```json
{
  "result": "CONDITIONAL",
  "roleEntityRef": "role:default/test",
  "pluginId": "catalog",
  "resourceType": "catalog-entity",
  "permissionMapping": ["read"],
  "conditions": {
    "rule": "IS_ENTITY_OWNER",
    "resourceType": "catalog-entity",
    "params": {
      "claims": ["group:default/team-a"]
    }
  }
}
```

This conditional policy can be used to display catalogs only if the user is a member of the owner group, or to display a list of all catalog user groups.

